sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K338042
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lucas Hartsough
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Construct assembled to allow the quantitative analysis of the heat shock promoter, <partinfo>K338001</partinfo>. Produces GFP in response to low-temperature heat shock.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The type of GFP used in this construct happens to have a very long half life. If growing cultures for fluorescence measurements, grow at 30°C - any higher will activate the promoter, causing GFP to be produced.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Registry of Standard Biological Parts

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1895003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM16_Newcastle
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter for molecular chaperone htpG. It is active during the heat shock response.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
This is a correction to part [http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_J45504 BBa_J45504], also the htpG Heat Shock Promoter. The original part contains a fragment of the coding sequence for molecular chaperone htpG (base pairs >287) which can be confirmed by [http://blast.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/ BLASTing the sequence]. This part contains only the first 287 bases of the original part which consist solely of the htpG promoter.
You can see the difference between the two sequences in the image below.
[[File:T--Newcastle--htpG-Seq-Comparison.png]]

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K338062
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP Reporter Device, Heat-Shock or IPTG Induced
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lucas Hartsough
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Construct assembled to allow the quantitative analysis of the heat shock/LacI promoter/repressor system, <partinfo>BBa_K338002</partinfo>. Produces GFP in response to low-temperature heat shock, more-so in the presence of LacI. GFP production is retarded in LacIq cells (or in the presence of +5mM glucose) about 4-6x. See K338002 for more detailed data.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The type of GFP used in this construct happens to have a very long half life. If growing cultures for fluorescence measurements, grow at 30??C - any higher will activate the promoter, causing GFP to be produced.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Registry of Standard Biological Parts

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K338081
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lucas Hartsough
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Intermediate designed to accelerate cloning of the HSP promoter (<partinfo>BBa_K338001</partinfo>) by adding an RBS downstream.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Designed to be ligated upstream of the desired heat-shock product. Keep in mind that the promoter is somewhat leaky and that cultures should be grown at 30°C.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Registry of Standard Biological Parts

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HSP-LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: K338001+R0011: Heat Shock Promoter + LacI Regulated Promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: 2010 Caltech iGEM Team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Fused heat shock promoter with lacI regulated promoter. It possesses the characteristic of both heat shock promoter and LacI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was designed to address the issue of a leaky promoter in front of a bacterial gene in an effort to create a genetic switch just for growth/cloning

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112400
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter for grpE gene - Heat Shock and Ultrasound Sensitive
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Christina Brown
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: According to Vollmer, et. al in their 1998 Applied and Enviormental Microbiology paper, "Bacterial Stress Responses to 1-Megahertz Pulsed Ultrasound in the Presence of Microbubble", the promoter for the grpE gene, a known heat shock promoter, is upregulated 24 times when cells are exposed to high frequency ultrasound and microbubble cavitation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: cloned from E. coli MG1655 genome
